        "text": "2 Timothy 4:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"They shall turn away their ears from the truth, and shall be turned unto fables.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "To draw away the disciples",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e. to",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " induce Christians to leave the communion and doctrine of the Church, and join their heresy. The A.V., \"to draw away disciples,\" is manifestly wrong; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "τοὺς μαθητὰς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " are Christ's disciples. For the general statement, see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 3:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"They which creep into houses, and lead captive silly women;\" and comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 16:17, 18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
